WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.760
RStudio Cloud allows us to create assignments for our learners via RStudio Projects.

00:00:08.760 --> 00:00:13.480
By creating assignments within an RStudio Cloud workspace, we set up a shared environment

00:00:13.480 --> 00:00:17.639
for our learners to access and complete their work.

00:00:17.639 --> 00:00:21.480
Assignments in RStudio Cloud happen at the project level.

00:00:21.480 --> 00:00:26.320
To create a new assignment, we click on the New Project button here in the top right.

00:00:26.320 --> 00:00:31.040
Once we're inside our project, we can create any files we'd like our students to use as

00:00:31.040 --> 00:00:33.700
part of completing the assignment.

00:00:33.700 --> 00:00:38.080
This could include an R Markdown document with instructions, an R script with partially

00:00:38.080 --> 00:00:45.119
completed code, or any other type of file available to you from within RStudio.

00:00:45.119 --> 00:00:49.279
After we create everything needed to get an assignment together, we'll want to make sure

00:00:49.279 --> 00:00:53.439
that our learners can access it by clicking on the Project Settings button in the upper

00:00:53.439 --> 00:00:58.720
right, clicking on the Access panel, and from the Who can view this project drop-down

00:00:58.720 --> 00:01:01.259
menu, choosing Everyone.

00:01:01.259 --> 00:01:05.800
The final step to making this an assignment is to check the box next to Make this project

00:01:05.800 --> 00:01:07.599
an assignment.

00:01:07.599 --> 00:01:11.959
When we navigate back to our workspace by clicking on the workspace name at the top,

00:01:11.959 --> 00:01:15.360
we see that our project is now listed as an assignment.

00:01:15.360 --> 00:01:19.599
Our learners will see a corresponding tag that says either Start, if they haven't yet

00:01:19.599 --> 00:01:24.559
opened the assignment, or Continue, if they've already opened the assignment.

00:01:24.559 --> 00:01:28.959
One thing to note is that if we make changes to an assignment, they will not be applied

00:01:28.959 --> 00:01:34.320
to any copies of the assignment that students have already created by opening the assignment.

00:01:34.320 --> 00:01:39.000
The changes we make to an assignment will only apply to future copies of the assignment.

